{
  "texts": [
    "The physics of MPCMs fundamentally differs from traditional approaches to controlling wave-matter interactions (see Supplementary Note 1).",
    "Generally speaking, the transfer function of a linear system is related to the inverse of the system's interaction matrix.",
    "The diagonal [resp.",
    "off-diagonal] entries of the interaction matrix capture the local [resp.",
    "non-local] properties of the primary entities that make up the system, i.e., their polarizabilities [resp."
  ]
}